    <!-- activity_faq -->
    <string name="faq_text">
        What is Shell\n
        Shell lets you have greater control over your launch procedures. Shell acts the same way that
        a regular Folder would - but it also extends that functionality by giving you, the user, control
        over what sound is played when you open the folder, what the outside of the folder looks like, 
        and what the contents of the folder are! You want files? Put it in the folder! You want apps? Put
        it in the folder!\n\n
        
        How do I get started?\n
        Simple! Place the Shell widget somewhere on your home screen. Then open this app again, and select a 
        sound or song to play by tapping the "App Sound" button. It will automatically drop you into your Music 
        folder. From there, you can choose a song, or browse elsewhere for different sounds. Then, tap the "App Lock"
        button to select a password. You can also select "My Files" to choose what files you want easy access to from
        within the Shell folder, as well as "My Apps" to select which applications you want to store within the Shell
        folder.\n\n 
    </string>

